Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Future direction", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.832335989380006*^9, 3.832335995602777*^9}, {
  3.898207468826923*^9, 
  3.898207473109272*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e72276cb-d5a1-4753-a77f-\
52f4dffed57b"],

Cell["\<\
Executing the mass transfer simulation in a grid graph could be the first \
step towards simulating the aggregation of mass in a random graph. In the \
Wolfram model framework, the space-time is represented by discrete hypergraph \
structure. Generating the functions developed in this work to hypergraph \
model would make this study interesting.
This project could be taken farther by using the package GRAVITAS, which has \
been developed recently. By utilising this package we can create discrete \
hypergraph structure of space-time for any metric. Running these functions on \
FLRW space-time.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8021862859717093`*^9, 3.8021862866993*^9}, {
   3.802186780928506*^9, 3.802186861789569*^9}, {3.8323359350826187`*^9, 
   3.832335937574898*^9}, {3.8323360079148006`*^9, 3.832336026898738*^9}, 
   3.8982074802548656`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"633b4e87-c2f6-4dae-89fe-\
148b34b3c1d5"]
}, Open  ]],

